workflow.name: Fetch daily job postings from JSearch to Google Sheets and Telegram
workflow.description:
This workflow automatically fetches job postings from the JSearch API once per day, filters out duplicates, and saves only new jobs to a Google Sheet. It also sends a Telegram summary with the number of newly added jobs.

### What this workflow does
‚Ä¢ Builds a custom job search query  
‚Ä¢ Fetches job listings from JSearch  
‚Ä¢ Loads existing job IDs from Google Sheets  
‚Ä¢ Removes already-saved jobs  
‚Ä¢ Writes only new jobs into the sheet  
‚Ä¢ Sends a Telegram summary with job count  

### Why it's useful
‚Ä¢ Hands-free daily job monitoring  
‚Ä¢ No duplicates ‚Äî clean data tracking  
‚Ä¢ Uses rate-limit-safe writing  
‚Ä¢ Easy to customize search keywords  
‚Ä¢ Works entirely with no-code steps  

### Requirements
‚Ä¢ RapidAPI (JSearch) account  
‚Ä¢ Google Sheets account  
‚Ä¢ Telegram Bot token  

### Ideal For
‚Ä¢ Job researchers  
‚Ä¢ Recruitment automations  
‚Ä¢ Personal job-search tracking  
‚Ä¢ Data collection workflows

nodes.name: Combine API Results with Existing IDs

parameters.content:
### Query Building and Querying Section
* Defines search text, encodes it
* Fetches job results from the API
* Splits them into individual items

### Existing-ID Filtering Section
*  Loads existing job IDs from the sheet
* Matches API results against them
* Removes duplicates
* Counts how many new jobs remain for processing

### Saving & Reporting Section
* Iterates through new jobs
* Applies a small delay to respect Google API limits
* Writes each job to the sheet
* Combines results
* Sends a Telegram summary

## How it works
This workflow runs once per day and automatically collects new job postings from the JSearch API.
It builds a search query, fetches recent job listings, and splits the API response into individual jobs.
Before saving anything, it loads existing job IDs from a Google Sheet and filters out duplicates, ensuring each job is stored only once.
New jobs are then written to the sheet with structured fields (title, company, salary, links, location, etc.).
To avoid Google API rate limits, each write is slightly delayed.
At the end of the run, the workflow sends a Telegram message with a summary showing the number of new jobs added and a direct link to the sheet.
The goal is to provide a clean, automated daily job tracker that eliminates manual checks and duplicate entries.

## Setup steps
### Create a Google Sheet with matching headers
(Status, ID, Job Title, Company Name, Apply Link, Company Website, Source, Type, Direct Apply, Remote, Date Posted (UTC), Fetched At, Location, Google Link, Salary, Minimum, Maximum)
### Add credentials:
‚Ä¢ RapidAPI key for JSearch.
‚Ä¢ Google Sheets OAuth.
‚Ä¢ Telegram Bot token.
### Update placeholders:
‚Ä¢ [YOUR_JOB_NAME_HERE] in Set Search Parameters.
‚Ä¢ [YOUR_GOOGLE_SHEET_HERE] (Document ID + Sheet).
‚Ä¢ [YOUR_CHAT_ID_HERE] for Telegram.
### Enable the workflow and adjust the schedule time if needed.
